<Issue id="16240" key="FAB-3621" number="3621" project="10002" reporter="mastersingh24" assignee="muralisr" creator="mastersingh24" type="10001" summary="As a member of a network who runs a peer, I want to be able to support clients who transact with the network with a limited scope of permissions" priority="2" resolution="10000" status="6" created="2017-05-03 14:18:29.0" updated="2018-07-20 18:55:40.0" resolutiondate="2018-03-08 19:08:09.0" votes="8" watches="16" workflowId="38306"> <description><! CDATA Currently, access control is scoped by organization at the channel level. This means that clients / peers are interchangeable in many cases.  The desire here is to limit the scope of what clients who transact can actually do. Examples include:  1) Request endorsements and query chaincode 2) Submit transactions to the orderer 3) No access to gossip network 4) No access to blocks only to their transactions 5) Related to 4 - events payload should be limited to transaction IDs if that is what is used to asynchronously learn the status of their transaction     The original intent was to introduce the concept of client orgs  A design doc is at https://docs.google.com/document/d/1oaR7IlpNCV6udvLhDootRtoruEvOrxByYVN4BQ___0A  ></description> </Issue>
